  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To provide the usual tender reports - Monthly tender summary list, weekly tender list including submission date, LTA/Commercial tracking list, Tender succession in term of number and value over total monthly tendered - etc..</li>\n  <li>To collate all tender BQ (New and existing) and formulate into levels of the building with different fire services in preparation for bulk order of material and equipment.</li>\n  <li>To obtain equipment prices on tank, pumps, control valves, sprinkler heads, valves, hydrants, HR, FE, EST ....etc on project tender.</li>\n  <li>To liaise wih purchasing on the usual price bought for equipment/material on projects and to determine is it worthwhile to negotiate with supplers to fix prices for the next 6 months on the usual bought material.</li>\n  <li>To assist in project handover to PIC.</li>\n  <li>To assist to provide new project references in  ERP system.</li>\n  <li>To assist to determine and collate all sources of enquiries of tenders.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / Degree in Quantity Surveying, Construction Management or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of relevant work experience in construction industry.</li>\n  <li>Candidates with LTA project experience preferred.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office and other Measurement Software.</li>\n  <li>Meticulous and details oriented.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work with tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Show independency ability to multi-task, prioritize and organize tasks.</li>\n  <li>Singaporean &amp; Permanent Resident only.</li>\n</ul>",
